Detailed Description

Stores basic information about a species including how many elements belong to the species, its charge, and phase type.

◆ nAtoms() [1/2]

int nAtoms ( ) const
inline

Returns the total number of atoms in this species.

For example, C2H2 has 4 total atoms (2 Carbon and 2 Hydrogen atoms). Note that this does not include electrons in the calculation.

Returns the number of atoms of a particular element contained in this species.

For example calling nAtoms("C") for the C2H2 molecule would return 2.
